webpackJsonp([64738213772401],{814:function(e,t){e.exports={data:{site:{siteMetadata:{title:"weiran.co",author:"Weiran Zhang"}},markdownRemark:{id:"/Users/weiran/git/weiran/weiran.co/src/pages/blog/2013/2/samsung-hires-judge-who-issued-extreme-ruling-against-apple/index.md absPath of file >>> MarkdownRemark",html:'<p>FOSS Patents does some sleuthing and discoveres the judge that ordered Apple to publish an <a href="http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/technology-19989750">apology</a> to Samsung, and <a href="http://allthingsd.com/20121101/u-k-court-orders-apple-to-make-its-samsung-apology-more-apologetic/">then rewrite</a> that apology, is being paid by Samsung as a patent consultant:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>That said, this just doesn’t feel right. It gives the impression that a judge who deals Samsung’s number one rival a huge PR blow, in a way that I found very extreme and unjustified, will be generously rewarded. For that reason alone, I think both Samsung and Sir Robin Jacob should not have done this.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>I guess Samsung liked what they saw.</p>',frontmatter:{title:"Samsung hires judge who issued extreme ruling against Apple",date:"February 28, 2013",passthroughUrl:"http://www.fosspatents.com/2013/02/uk-judge-who-issued-extreme-ruling-for.html"}}},pathContext:{slug:"/blog/2013/2/samsung-hires-judge-who-issued-extreme-ruling-against-apple/",previous:{fields:{slug:"/blog/2013/2/no-one-left-to-speak-out/"},frontmatter:{title:"No one left to speak out",passthroughUrl:null}},next:{fields:{slug:"/blog/2013/3/vatican-commerates-the-pope-with-a-photo-album-typeset-in-comic-sans/"},frontmatter:{title:"Vatican commerates the pope with a photo album typeset in Comic Sans",passthroughUrl:"http://www.vatican.va/bxvi/omaggio/index_en.html"}}}}}});
